<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-11-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-11-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="141" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d141">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 6775/236.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">President of Salvador</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-11-23"><hi rend="italic">November 23,
                                    1907</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I acknowledge with much pleasure your telegram of the 19th communicating
                            the gratifying intelligence that peace and tranquillity have been
                            restored throughout your country.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Theodore
                            Roosevelt.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>